body:
@vasild 

> However, this PR is necessary for address relay to work properly and automatic connections to be made to CJDNS peers. I.e. to make CJDNS a first class citizen network like IPv4, IPv6, Tor and I2P.

Thanks for providing this motivation, it's helpful to understand the aim of this PR. Could you go a bit further and share your perspective on _why_ you think CJDNS should be a first class citizen network in bitcoin core? Does it provide different features / privacy / etc. from other networks? Or is this a case where you think optionality is good, so supporting more networks is better? Thanks in advance!

